<h2> Instructions </h2>

<p>
	Assemble the two objects together using the arrow keys (&#8592;,&#8593;,&#8595;,&#8594;). Play all four visualization methods!
</p>

<div class='btn-group-xs'>
	<button class='btn btn-default mode-button btn-block' title='choose visualization mode' id='button-full-state'>
		full-state
	</button>
	<button class='btn btn-default mode-button btn-block' title='choose visualization mode' id='button-graph'>
		region-based-mean±var
	</button>
	<button class='btn btn-default mode-button btn-block' title='choose visualization mode' id='button-mean±var'>
		mean±var
	</button>
	<button class='btn btn-default mode-button btn-block' title='choose visualization mode' id='button-mean'>
		mean
	</button>
</div>

<br>

<p>
	<strong>Full-state</strong> sensing provides the most information, because it provides the position of all robots (200 numbers for 100 robots).

	<br>

	<strong>Mean</strong> tells where the average position of the entire swarm is(just 2 numbers for all 100 robots), and knowing the <strong>variance</strong> adds only 3 additional numbers while showing a ring depicting the deviation from the mean.

	<br>

	<strong>Region-based mean and variance</strong> will add information by not only giving the mean and variance of the entire swarm but individual mean and variances for the robots close to each object as well.
</p>